# üöÄ feature request

### Relevant Package
@angular/core
@angular/common - maybe, not sure?

### Description
It would be nice to have possibility to use *static types* inside templates without need of putting them into component. 

Imagine that you have `Enum` or `Type<>` that you want to use in template, for example you have `ngIf` and you want to compare value of some property with `Enum` value. You have to do following in order to allow this comparison in your template.

``` ts
import {TestEnum} from './testEnum';

export class TestComponent
{
  //with some special directive syntax in template this could be removed
  public TestEnum = TestEnum;

  public testValue: TestEnum = TestEnum.Prva;
}
```

Asp.Net Core Razor syntax has something similar which is called *[directives](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/mvc/views/razor?view=aspnetcore-3.0#directives)* 

Angular templates have already special syntax, so i think this would be possible. 


### Describe the solution you'd like
In order to make it simpler (maybe not, im not specialist on angular template compilation), but it would be nice to have some special syntax at top of html template something like
`{{@import {TestEnum} from './testEnum';}}` or something which would extend context with property of same name and value passed from import. This *special directives* {{@directive expression}} could be used also for something different (maybe `{{@inject ElementRef}}`)

### Describe alternatives you've considered
Workaround is just to add it manualy to `Component`, but this `template directives` would be nicer.

As i said it would be nice, it is not necessary :).
Thx

